The body of the woman was found dumped outside a bar.A police officer at the scene said investigations into the gruesome murder had commenced. The body of a woman who is suspected to have been raped before being murdered was found on Saturday at Ngucui village in Kirinyaga County.
The body of the woman, who has since been identified as Millicent Wangeci Gitari, was found dumped outside a bar.
The 57-year-old woman's body had bruises in the neck, a hint that she may have been strangled by her attackers. Used condoms were also found at the scene.



